      {
        "id" : "e7514dbb-8271-40d8-ba38-8f236d1ac672",
        "parentId" : null,
        "authorId" : "70f6644c-c194-46d3-8fee-ab1357be1275",
        "body" : "This seems concerning, does conda not support pyproject.toml?",
        "createdAt" : "2020-10-22T12:20:09Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2020-10-22T12:52:47Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "70f6644c-c194-46d3-8fee-ab1357be1275",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "b382bd14-3dc8-48ab-9371-a913608ad97f",
        "parentId" : "e7514dbb-8271-40d8-ba38-8f236d1ac672",
        "authorId" : "9b22d183-e721-40a8-8482-d53064d1fbee",
        "body" : "I and others have done this on other feedstocks for conda forge. The PEP 517 change and pip's new behavior regarding it is a bit annoying. We don't build wheels in feedstocks and this is a way to disable that. I had trouble with the `--no-usepep-517` pip flag and `-no-binary` was confusing too. This worked.",
        "createdAt" : "2020-10-22T12:22:23Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2020-10-22T12:52:47Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "9b22d183-e721-40a8-8482-d53064d1fbee",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "eea88aca-b2a5-4f14-8ab4-63aa23e1b8f2",
        "parentId" : "e7514dbb-8271-40d8-ba38-8f236d1ac672",
        "authorId" : "9b22d183-e721-40a8-8482-d53064d1fbee",
        "body" : "> This seems concerning, does conda not support pyproject.toml?\r\n\r\nI think the answer to that is \"not really\", because the build is defined in the meta.yaml, build.sh, and build.bat files. `pyproject.toml` is redudant and conda doesn't read it to try to setup the build environment.",
        "createdAt" : "2020-10-22T12:28:54Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2020-10-22T12:52:47Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "9b22d183-e721-40a8-8482-d53064d1fbee",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      }
    ],
